The paper discusses compact representations of planning instances, which is a common concept in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and automated planning (cs.PL). The paper also discusses various criteria for efficient access to actions, which falls under data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses positive and negative results, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) as well.
